The Library of Congress, can you believe it?”ADAD“American history, my friend, think about that,” he added in a delighted voice.
ADADThe newest recording preserved by the Library of Congress is Jay-Z’s “The Blueprint,” which was released on Sept. 11, 2001.
The album, featuring soul-music-sampling production from a then-mostly unknown Kanye West, made Jay-Z a star and further pushed hip-hop music into mainstream pop consciousness.
According to the Library of Congress’s online directory, “The Blueprint” is only the eighth rap album to be inducted.